The article discusses the impact of tax cuts on the behavior of individuals and businesses. It mentions that over 100 companies have offered bonuses and benefit hikes to their workers as a result of the tax cut, benefiting approximately one million workers. The article also mentions that high tax rates in certain states have led to population loss, and some governors and mayors are considering converting income taxes into payroll taxes to preserve federal deductibility. The author argues that taxes have a significant influence on people's investment decisions, work and savings behavior, and where they choose to live. The article concludes by stating that lowering taxes on activities such as work, investment, starting a business, or saving for retirement will lead to an increase in these activities.